  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/ae30d99e27236749510e387520abf7be.avif?t=1753993305\" width=622 height=254 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/3049b53bd6af9ea2c05563237fdce8cb.poster.avif?t=1753993305\" width=602 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/3049b53bd6af9ea2c05563237fdce8cb.webm?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/3049b53bd6af9ea2c05563237fdce8cb.mp4?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Slidemagi is a turn-based strategy game in which units move by sliding the lines of the board. As a powerful Mage, you wield a deck of cards to cast spells and summon unique units, each with special abilities, to fight under your command.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Slidemagi is a duel between two mages on a 10x10 board. Each turn, you can make one move, which consists of one of the following:</p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Move a unit (the entire row moves).</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Cast a Spell (summon a new unit or cast a defensive/attacking spell).</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >At the end of each move, all of the player's units will attack in all four directions, if possible.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Each player has 16 cards to use in battle, which they can select before entering the fight. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The objective of the game is to defeat the enemy mage in battle mode or eliminate all enemy units in waves mode.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The game has two main modes of play: adventure mode, where you progress to unlock new spells and units, and player vs. player magical combat, where each Mage uses their deck to defeat the opponent.  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/3b47d6ddda2d3841e242291e2f2af346.avif?t=1753993305\" width=640 height=360 /></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Features: </h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Sliding</strong>: Units move by sliding the lines. When the move is made, all your units will execute their action. The position of units is important. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/0755c6fdac262b0687342941ef53d11a.poster.avif?t=1753993305\" width=640 height=150 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/0755c6fdac262b0687342941ef53d11a.webm?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/0755c6fdac262b0687342941ef53d11a.mp4?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Squeezing</strong>: By sliding, other units can become squeezed into their line, allowing dangerous terrain to be placed beneath them.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/5870095591d0a531e997043bb265f603.poster.avif?t=1753993305\" width=640 height=150 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/5870095591d0a531e997043bb265f603.webm?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/5870095591d0a531e997043bb265f603.mp4?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Mages and Spells</strong>: You are the Mage! You must defeat the enemy in a magical combat. Use your deck of cards to cast powerful spells and summon new units.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/36483bae0fba66515106b2d0f5c61aec.poster.avif?t=1753993305\" width=640 height=150 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/36483bae0fba66515106b2d0f5c61aec.webm?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/36483bae0fba66515106b2d0f5c61aec.mp4?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Graves and Raise Dead</strong>: When a unit dies, a grave appears, which the Necromancer can revive. As all objects lock the line on the edge when sliding, this is a fundamental part of the game, leading to open or closed games.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/e146d40d2745d05ec2918e51da35fd68.poster.avif?t=1753993305\" width=640 height=150 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/e146d40d2745d05ec2918e51da35fd68.webm?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/e146d40d2745d05ec2918e51da35fd68.mp4?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Chain Reactions</strong>: Certain moves can cause chain reactions. For example, killing enemies and having a Necromancer to revive them in the same turn.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/e93e6d75c66153d2b3e5c8303b117680.poster.avif?t=1753993305\" width=640 height=150 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/e93e6d75c66153d2b3e5c8303b117680.webm?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/e93e6d75c66153d2b3e5c8303b117680.mp4?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Deck Building</strong>: Before going into the battle, choose a set of spells from the available spell cards. Deck composition will depend on your strategy and the characteristics of the terrain you'll be playing on. The deck is shuffled, and you will have five spells available at any given time. Chance also plays a role.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/649873ff8a0e2876c4035cb1638843f3.poster.avif?t=1753993305\" width=602 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/649873ff8a0e2876c4035cb1638843f3.webm?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/649873ff8a0e2876c4035cb1638843f3.mp4?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Spell Cards and Units: There are dozens of unit types and spells to use and combine to craft your strategy. Each type of unit performs a specific action. For example, Spiders shoot a web that traps the enemy and makes them very vulnerable; Scorpions, poison their enemies, etc. There are melee and ranged units, weak and powerful units, grounded and flying units, etc.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/c13e42bcbd288be7be39071bc8b6c84a.poster.avif?t=1753993305\" width=640 height=150 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/c13e42bcbd288be7be39071bc8b6c84a.webm?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/c13e42bcbd288be7be39071bc8b6c84a.mp4?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Many Modes of Play: Dive into adventure mode to discover and master new spells, or enjoy friendly competition in both local and online multiplayer magical duels.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Slidemagi is a game with an original design, developed by BATOVI Games, a studio from Montevideo, Uruguay.</strong></p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/ae30d99e27236749510e387520abf7be.avif?t=1753993305\" width=622 height=254 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/3049b53bd6af9ea2c05563237fdce8cb.poster.avif?t=1753993305\" width=602 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/3049b53bd6af9ea2c05563237fdce8cb.webm?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2347340/extras/3049b53bd6af9ea2c05563237fdce8cb.mp4?t=1753993305\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Slidemagi is a turn-based strategy game in which units move by sliding the lines of the board. As a powerful Mage, you wield a deck of cards to cast spells and summon unique units, each with special abilities, to fight under your command.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Slidemagi is a duel between two mages on a 10x10 board. Each turn, you can make one move, which consists of one of the following:</p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Move a unit (the entire row moves).</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Cast a Spell (summon a new unit or cast a defensive/attacking spell).</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >At the end of each move, all of the player's units will attack in all four directions, if possible.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Each player has 16 cards to use in battle, which they can select before entering the fight. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The objective of the game is to defeat the enemy mage in battle mode or eliminate all enemy units in waves mode.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The game has two 